  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Uncertainty quantification was performed across rheological and geometric input parameters; a screening sensitivity study was conducted verbally as part of the UQ workflow to identify which parameters contributed most to hemolysis index variance, confirming that fluid viscosity and impeller tip clearance were leading contributors. Monte Carlo sampling (n=500) yielded a 95th-percentile RH of 0.87, well below the acceptance threshold of 1.0.",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
