      "rationale": "All 13 input parameters (geometric tolerances, fluid properties, boundary conditions) documented with nominal values and sources. Uncertainty ranges assigned based on manufacturer tolerances and literature. Monte Carlo sampling (n=500, Latin hypercube) propagated input uncertainties to RH output. 95th-percentile RH = 0.87 < 1.0. A screening sensitivity study was conducted as part of the UQ workflow and verbally identified fluid viscosity and impeller tip clearance as dominant contributors; these findings informed the UQ parameter prioritization. Achieves Gradation 2."
