    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required gradation levels for MRL 2. Six factors accepted at Gradation 1 per MRL 2 scoping. Uncertainty quantification via Monte Carlo sampling demonstrates 95th-percentile RH = 0.87, providing margin below the RH < 1.0 acceptance criterion. The UQ workflow incorporated a screening sensitivity study that verbally confirmed viscosity and tip clearance as leading variance contributors, supporting confidence in the UQ results. The model is accepted as fit for the stated COU of identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device.",
